While there is no doubt that the initiation step in 
the protolytic cracking of paraffins and cracking of 
olefins is the formation of a carbocation or a carbe- 
nium ion-like intermediate on a Bronsted acid site 
of the zeolite, it is still under discussion if paraffin 
cracking initiation via carbenium ions also occur and, 
if so, on what zeolite sites are the carbenium ions 
formed. 
Some authors have claimed that a carbenium ion 
can be formed on alkanes or cycloalkanes 
by abstrac- 
