branched isomer, requires more space to form the 
reaction intermediate, with possible limitations by 
the pore size of ZSM-5 zeolite. By carrying out this 
selective cracking of molecules in the gasoline range, 
the addition of ZSM-5 to FCC catalysts produces an 
increase in gasoline RON and also an increase in the 
production of propylene. 
